main event: Two glowing objects were observed to be stationary in the sky over Trenton, New Jersey for 6 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were compared in size to the moon.
Glowing lights were observed on the objects.
The objects were stationary and visually observed for 10 minutes.
The sighting was concluded as probably being caused by an aircraft.
The report mentions obtaining a photograph of the objects through the 'Charlie Section' for further evaluation.
witnesses: one witness, John Booine, age 39, Assistant Commander of Air Cadet Training
photographs: The report mentions obtaining a photograph, but no photograph is included in the provided text.
